[4] Cholera - Sudan (Kassala State)
Date: Sun 29 Oct 2017
Source: Reliefweb, a Radio Dabanga report [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/sudan/two-die-cholera-sudan-s-kassala


Two women died and 2 other people were infected with cholera at Aroma locality of Kassala state last week [week ending 29 Oct 2017]. Ahmed Hasan Dirar told Radio Dabanga that one of the cholera patients was transferred to Kassala Hospital in critical condition, while the other patient is still in a temporary isolation center. He said that the deaths occurred on [Tue 24 Oct 2017].

He said last [Thu 26 Oct 2017] the State Health Ministry sent a committee to Aroma to find out [about] the cases. He also stressed that Aroma Hospital is lacking doctors and is run by medical assistants in a very poor environment.

Sudan's first cases of cholera were recorded in Blue Nile state in August 2016. Since then, the disease spread in eastern Sudan, and later to the Northern State and central Sudan's El Gezira. In April 2017, sources in White Nile state reported a rapid spread of cholera. The disease then spread to North Kordofan, and fully hit Khartoum in May 2017.

The epidemic - referred to as "acute watery diarrhea" by the Sudanese government and several international agencies operating in Sudan - quickly spread in the camps for displaced people in Darfur when the 1st cases emerged in the region in June 2017.

--
